items.title: Sailor Moon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Sailor Moon Wiki!
items.desc:
The Sailor Moon Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to the metaseries Sailor Moon. 

"Bishōjo Senshi Sailor Moon" refers to the original incarnation of Sailor Moon, which was a manga created and illustrated by Naoko Takeuchi and later adapted to a popular anime series that spanned 200 episodes, three feature films, five specials, and five memorials. Other adaptions of the Sailor Moon series include a live-action TV series, a series of musicals, and a second anime adaption that premiered in July 2014. 

New editors are welcome! We are really grateful for any help on pages, templates, and other things that can improve this wiki!

items.name: Sailor Moon Wiki
items.title: Sailor Moon Wiki
items.headline: Bienvenidos a Sailor Moon Wiki
items.desc: Sailor Moon Wiki es un proyecto de base de datos de la franquicia Sailor Moon''. Se inició en Octubre de 2009, y existen aproximadamente 650 artículos. Este proyecto es una wiki, por lo que cualquiera puede editarla. ¡No dudes en compartir tus conocimientos! El proyecto en sí, consiste en recopilar de la obra Pretty Soldier Sailor Moon (美少女戦士セーラームーン Bishōjo Senshi Sērā Mūn), un manga perteneciente al género Shōjo creado por Naoko Takeuchi en 1992. Más conocida simplemente como Sailor Moon, la serie se hizo particularmente famosa por volver a popularizar con gran éxito el subgénero de las magical girls,2 y sus elementos sentai consiguieron que la aceptación también fuese masiva entre el sector masculino, generalmente menos interesado en este tipo de historias.3 Fue publicada en la revista japonesa Nakayoshi ("Amigas íntimas") de la editorial Kodansha entre 1992 y 1997 y recopilada en 18 tankoubon (volúmenes). En el 2012, por motivo de conmemorar los 25 años de aniversario de la serie, Toei Animation y Naoko Takeuchi, deciden hacer un "reboot" de la serie con nuevos diseños, pero conservando la historia del manga, conocido como Sailor Moon Crystal.

items.headline: Sailor Moon Anime Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to the Sailor Moon Anime Wikia! This wikia focuses on the English anime adaptation of the Sailor Moon series. The series follows Serena Tsukino (whom the watchers of the Japanese and the readers of the manga know as Usagi), who transforms into Sailor Moon to fight evil like the Negaverse, Alan and Ann, the Negamoon Family, and more! Enter now to learn about the English anime and how you can help the wikia grow!

items.headline: Olympians (Sailor Moon ReVersion)
items.desc: This wiki is dedicated to fanaticism of the Sailor Moon Series, the collection of the Greco-Roman Mythology Classics and the modernized version of the anime series by colliding the classics becoming the Guardians of Olympus. Enjoy the adventure! Putting the two together. Sailor Moon + Greco-Roman Mythology = Olympians. The mythical action-adventures of a college girl who learns of her destiny as the mystical warrior Guardian Moon and must band together with the other Guardian Warriors to defend the Mortal Land and the Skies of the Gods. Life can be tough when you're in college. Enter Selina Chase, an average, if somewhat clumsy, first-year student whose cravings for sports and capacity for patients are offset by her enthusiasm for life. Her normal existence is suddenly turned upside down when a strange woman in black named Luna Lupo comes into her life. Suddenly, Selina finds herself with the ability to transform into the superhero known as Guardian Moon. Fighting the occasional monster may be the least of her worries, though...
